object.customQuery:
SELECT distinct personinfo.SystemId, personinfo.ParentId, personinfo.CMMContainer, personinfo.Id, personinfo.PersonTypeCd, personinfo.GenderCd, personinfo.BirthDt, personinfo.MaritalStatusCd, personinfo.OccupationClassCd, personinfo.EmployerCd, personinfo.PositionTitle, personinfo.BestWayToContact, personinfo.BestTimeToContact, personinfo.Age, personinfo.YearsLicensed, personinfo.OccupationOtherDesc, personinfo.OccupationOtherJointDesc, personinfo.YouthfulInd, personinfo.EducationCd, personinfo.OccupationCd, personinfo.RowId 
FROM
 personinfo
where personinfo.cmmcontainer='Policy'
and personinfo.systemid in (select systemid from advrxxchangedbeans where concat(adddt,addtm)>='$$m_strtdt' and concat(adddt,addtm) <='$$m_Enddt' and
 cmmcontainer='Policy')

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: Exp_format_dates

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))
